snippet.textDisplay: I am an Indian and I boldly want to admit that Coke Studio Pakistan is doing great job and producing some of the finest and most heart-touching songs that I have ever heard. I do feel that Coke Studio Pakistan is better than Coke Studio@MTV when it comes to the quality of music being composed. Also I do regret that this image of Pakistani culture is often shadowed and tarnished by some crazy people committing jihad and mercilessly slaughtering innocent people solely in the name of protecting one's religion. Being a Hindu, I can assert that no religion whatsoever validates the killing of any innocent human being. Why do we again and again forget that we all are alike and so much to the extent that I cannot merely differentiate a Pakistani person from an Indian one just going by their looks or the language they speak. I will pray to the Almighty that peace will be restored someday and we all will be happy looking each other. God bless.
